-- N.Y. Giants Running Back Ahmad Bradshaw to Miss Game At Atlanta
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2012-12-14T21:30:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-14/n-y-giants-running-back-ahmad-bradshaw-to-miss-game-at-atlanta.html
The New York Giants will be missing
leading rusher  Ahmad Bradshaw  for their National Football League
game in two days at the  Atlanta Falcons .  Bradshaw, 26, was ruled out of the game today because of
knee and foot injuries. He has not practiced all week.  Bradshaw has 196 carries for 869 yards and five touchdowns
this season, more than half the team’s total of carries (339)
and yards rushing (1,513) in 2012. He also has 21 receptions for
196 yards.  The Giants (8-5) lead the National Football Conference East
division by one game over the Washington Redskins and Dallas
Cowboys. The Falcons (11-2) have the NFC’s best record and have
clinched the NFC South division title.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  